cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically image harmonization. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves generating synthesized composite images, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). The proposed method is a deep learning approach, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves domain verification, which is a technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel domain verification discriminator, which is a type of adversarial training, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
